{{multiple issues| {{BLP sources|date=April 2011}} {{notability|bio|date=February 2011}} }}
'''Richard Helmut Grathoff''' was a [[Phenomenology (psychology)|phenomenologist]] and Professor [[Emeritus]] in the Department of [[Sociology]] at [[Bielefeld University]], [[Germany]].<ref name="Srubar2005">{{cite book|last=Srubar|first=Ilja|title=Development of sociology in Japan|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Em-gp7fdpxEC&pg=PA160|accessdate=16 April 2011|date=2005-01-17|publisher=VS Verlag|isbn=978-3-531-14513-6|page=160}}</ref><ref name="Ritzer1996">{{cite book|last=Ritzer|first=George|title=Classical sociological theory|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_yZFAAAAYAAJ|accessdate=16 April 2011|year=1996|publisher=McGraw-Hill|isbn=978-0-07-053017-1|page=389}}</ref>
Born on August 30, 1934 in [[Unna]], [[Westphalia]], [[Germany]], he received his Ph.D. from the [[New School for Social Research]] in 1969 after studying under [[Aron Gurwitsch]], [[Thomas Luckmann]] and [[Peter L. Berger]]. Influenced by [[Charles Sanders Peirce]], [[Edmund Husserl]] and [[Alfred Schutz]], his work has included research in the topics of [[natural environment|milieu]] and [[life-world]] ("[[Lebenswelt]]") and [[contemporary social theory]]. He died in [[Oerlinghausen]], Germany on November 10, 2013.<ref>[http://www.nw-trauer.de/Traueranzeige/Richard-Grathoff]</ref>
==Major works==
*The Structure of Social Inconsistencies (1970) *Maurice Merleau-Ponty und das Problem der Struktur in den Sozialwissenschaften (coed.) (1976) *The Theory of Social Action: The Correspondence of Alfred Schutz and Talcott Parsons (1978) *Alfred Schutz und die Idee des Alltags in den Sozialwissenschaften (coed.) (1979) *Sozialitat und Intersubjektivitat (coed.) (1983) *Alfred Schutz und Aron Gurwitsch: Briefwechsel 1939-1959 (1985) *Philosophers in Exile: The Correspondence of Alfred Schutz and Aron Gurwitsch (1989) *Milieu und Lebenswelt (1989)
